text: David Brown (born March 15, 1981), better known as Young Buck or Buck for short, is an American rapper.'Young Buck', Billboard (Nov 4, 2006), p. 34 He is from Nashville, Tennessee.Tamara Palmer, Country Fried Soul: Adventures in Dirty South Hip-hop (San Francisco, CA: Backbeat, 2005), pp. 78-79 He is best known for his albums 'Buck The World' and 'Straight Outta Cashville'. Brown is the founder and president of his own record label Ca$hville Records. ==References== Category:1981 births Category:Gangsta rappers Category:Living people Category:African-American rappers Category:Rappers from Tennessee Category:Musicians from Nashville, Tennessee
